John is the hapless narrator ofCat's Cradle.In the past, he set out to write a book about the day the atomic bomb was dropped on Hiroshima, entitledThe Day the World Ended.His research led him to an ill-fated acquaintance with Angela, Frank, and Newt Hoenikker, the equally hapless children of Felix Hoenikker. He became involved with their efforts to buy happiness through the use of their father's scientific creation,ice- nine,which could simply and without effort turn water to ice.